The problem in the given program is that there isn't a 'score' property in 
the user object but an 'points' one. In Tundra, you need to refer correctly
correctly to the properties of your objects to avoid errors like this one. 
Here is the corrected source code :

```Tundra
val report = {
  user: {
    name: "Ada",
    score: 10
  },
  bonus: 2
};

val total = report.user.score + report.bonus;
print(total);
```
